comment: Abrines (OKC) and Hood (UTA) briefly engage and separate off ball.
Abrines (OKC) does not give Hood (UTA) room to land on the jump shot attempt.
Johnson (UTA) intentionally kicks the ball on the play.
Adams (OKC) makes marginal contact with Hill (UTA) following the screen.
Gobert (UTA) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Westbrook (OKC) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
RATR shows that Hill (UTA) makes contact with Westbrook's (OKC) arm that affects his SQBR.
Hood (UTA) sets the screen on Westbrook (OKC) and the two players briefly engage and separate.
[Observable in enhanced video] Johnson (UTA) slides his pivot foot.
Adams (OKC) legally contests Johnson's (UTA) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Westbrook (OKC) pushes Gobert (UTA) and dislodges him from his rebounding position.
Hill (UTA) does not beat Westbrook (OKC) to the spot and is not in a legal guarding position at the time of the contact.
Hayward (UTA) releases the pass prior to landing.
Westbrook (OKC) legally contests Hill's (UTA) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
[Observable in enhanced video] Johnson (UTA) moves his pivot foot.
Adams (OKC) maintains legal guarding position on the drive to the basket by Johnson (UTA).
Hayward (UTA) commits a take foul on Grant (OKC).
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of UTA possession stands.
